CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1969, pg. 17 reads: "Pan-Hellenic Council - Representatives from the five major Greek letter organizations met recently and formed the Pittsburgh Pan-Hellenic Association. New officers and representatives are pictured above.  From left to right: Eva Terry, Vice Chairman, Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority; William Fisher, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity; Judith Nelson, an advisor of the undergrad chapter of AKA's; George Charlton, Kappa Alpha Psi, treasurer; Janet Thompson, past Basileus of AKA's; Dr. John Hairston, Omega Phi Psi Fraternity; James Boyd, Omegas, sergeant-at-arms; Harold White, chairman, Alpha Phi Alpha; Lenore Ivey, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, secretary; Arthur Burt, Kappas, and Diana Williams, Deltas. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Pan-Hellenic Council Representatives, from left: Eva Terry, William Fisher, Judith Nelson, George Charlton, Janet Thompson, Dr. John Hairston, James Boyd, Harold White, Lenore Ivey, Arthur Burt, and Diana Williams, gathered in domestic interior with pointed doorway in background
